  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#  Automatic Zoning Procedure (AZP) algorithm\n",
    "**Authors: [Xin Feng](https://github.com/xf37)** \n",
    "\n",
    "AZP can work with different types of objective functions, which are very sensitive to aggregating data from a large number of zones into a pre-designated smaller number of regions.\n",
    "\n",
    "AZP was originally formulated in [Openshaw, 1977](https://www.jstor.org/stable/622300?casa_token=QITLwNVUPj4AAAAA%3AKXYVQHrdeAtefxZKkvxxUrWA_QCedSJrZwQD36F16Jfqx7Vq47uu1G_vp9I085Iozy_roZ_Dh6qQopZ6yXjfPsy4Y2aBqso-l0wZS2YqNv9pkh1JNXc&seq=1#metadata_info_tab_contents) and then extended in [Openshaw, S. and Rao, L. (1995)](https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.461.8982&rep=rep1&type=pdf)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:57.736396Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:56.376752Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",

    "import libpysal\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../\")\n",
    "from spopt.region import AZP"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "## Mexican State Regional Income Clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "To illustrate `azp` we utilize data on regional incomes for Mexican states over the period 1940-2000, originally used in [Rey and Sastré-Gutiérrez (2010)](https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/17421772.2010.493955?casa_token=r6iIZaEKaywAAAAA%3ARxjQkEOcxQ5gffa1EGyd2rByA6w0uVxg5cU3v4VaSmx2u89Nr3oSe2f_n63CV20Ysrjs07U47m98). \n",
    "\n",
    "We can first explore the data by plotting the per capital gross regional domestic product (in constant USD 2000 dollars) for each year in the sample, using a quintile classification:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:57.990163Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:57.888442Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pth = libpysal.examples.get_path('mexicojoin.shp')\n",
    "mexico = gpd.read_file(pth)"
   ]
  },

    "for year in range(1940, 2010, 10):\n",
    "    ax = mexico.plot(column=f'PCGDP{year}', scheme='Quantiles', cmap='GnBu', edgecolor='b', legend=True)\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Regionalization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we specify a number of parameters that will serve as input to the `azp` model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The variables in the dataframe that will be used to measure regional dissimilarity:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.540597Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.535932Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['PCGDP1950', 'PCGDP1960', 'PCGDP1970', 'PCGDP1980', 'PCGDP1990', 'PCGDP2000']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "attrs_name = [f'PCGDP{year}' for year in range(1950,2010, 10)]\n",
    "attrs_name"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A [spatial weights object](https://pysal.org/libpysal/tutorial.html) expresses the spatial connectivity of the zones:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.557770Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.542235Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "w = libpysal.weights.Queen.from_dataframe(mexico)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The number of regions that we would like to aggregate these zones into:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.562507Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.560607Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_clusters = 5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are four optional parameters. In this example, we only use the default settings, you can define them as needed.\n",
    "\n",
    "allow_move_strategy: For a different behavior for allowing moves, an AllowMoveStrategy instance can be passed as argument.\n",
    "\n",
    "    class: AllowMoveStrategy or None, default: None\n",
    "                       \n",
    "random_state: Random seed.\n",
    "\n",
    "    None, int, str, bytes, or bytearray, default: None\n",
    "            \n",
    "initial_labels: One-dimensional array of labels at the beginning of the algorithm.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    class: numpy.ndarray or None, default: None\n",
    "    If None, then a random initial clustering will be generated.  \n",
    "\n",
    "objective_func: the objective function to use.\n",
    "\n",
    "    class: spopt.region.objective_function.ObjectiveFunction, default: ObjectiveFunctionPairwise()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The model can then be solved:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.752328Z",
     "start_time": "2021-06-28T20:57:59.566263Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "n_regions_per_comp {0: 5}\n",
      "comp_label 0\n",
      "n_regions_in_comp 5\n",
      "Regions in comp: {0, 1, 2, 3, 4}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model = AZP(mexico, w, attrs_name, n_clusters)\n",
    "model.solve()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {

    }
   },
   "outputs": [],

    "    \n",
    "    model = AZP(mexico, w, year, 5)\n",
